<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-12-24T15:49:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-12-24T15:49:00-05:00" n="578" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d578">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.51/374.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-12-24T16:00:00-04:49">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 24, 1914, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Bill for issue of eight million gourdes paper money promulgated. It does
                            not contemplate participation or assistance by the Bank in advance of
                            reversion. There is no clause providing that in case of an agreement
                            with the Bank the issue will not be made. Extra session of Congress
                            closed yesterday.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>